-ton-io|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u039a\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b4\u03b5\u03cd\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03cc\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03b9\u03cc|last=Newsroom|date=14 March 2020|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> Also, a 67-year-old man hospitalised in Zakynthos died, bringing the country death toll to three.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsbomb.gr/ellada/story/1062718/koronoios-tritos-nekros-stin-ellada|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a4\u03c1\u03af\u03c4\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1|last=Newsroom|website=Newsbomb|language=el|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> Testing strategy shifted to only elderly, severely ill, and healthcare personnel. It is announced by Dr. Sotiris Tsiodras{{efn|Sotiris Tsiodras became known as the \u201cnew beloved of Greeks\u201d by ''[[Le Figaro]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/international/l-infectiologue-sotirios-tsiodras-nouvelle-coqueluche-des-grecs-20200320|title=L\u2019infectiologue Sotirios Tsiodras, nouvelle coqueluche des Grecs|website=Le Figaro|language=French|date=20 March 2020}}</ref> in which he asked the Prime Minister [[Kyriakos Mitsotakis]] for strict lockdown measures as soon as the first cases were noted in Italy. Greek sociologist Andreas Drymiotis wrote: \u201cGreeks particularly appreciate his calm, his knowledge on the matter, and his deep respect for all victims and the fact that he has an unbreakable dedication to nursing staff.\u201d<ref>{{cite web|url=https://neoskosmos.com/en/161116/sydney-born-immunologist-sotiris-tsiodras-the-voice-of-coronavirus-in-greece/|title=Sydney-born immunologist Sotiris Tsiodras, the \u2018voice\u2019 of coronavirus in Greece|website=Neos Kosmos|language=French|date=24 March 2020}}</ref>}} in EODY Press Release<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eody.gov.gr