3b1 - 95 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 |last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-29|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref> The first case of coronavirus was reported on the monastery at [[Mount Athos]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://greekcitytimes.com/2020/03/29/first-case-of-coronavirus-at-mount-athos/|title=First case of coronavirus at Mount Athos|last=Greek City Times|date=2020-03-29|website=greekcitytimes.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n*On 30 March, 56 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the county total to 1212. Five more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 43.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/213373/koronoios-43-thanatoi-56-nea-kroysmata-sta-1-212-synolika|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 43 \u03b8\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03b9, 56 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1, \u03c3\u03c4\u03b1 1.212 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac |last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-30|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n*On 31 March, 102 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1314. Six more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 49.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/213525/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 49 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 - 82 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03b2\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b9\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-31|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> Twenty of the cases are aboard a passenger ship stationed out of the port of Piraeus. It carried 382 persons, including 36 Greeks, 150 Turks, 83 Indonesians and others. At least some of the persons were Turkish workers travelling to Spain but the ship was turned back to Turkey when the cases were identified. It was not accepted in Turkey and since 21st of March is at Piraeus.<ref>[https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-karantina-peiraia-kroyazieroploio \"Coronavirus: In quarantine at Piraeus the cruiser 'El. Venizelos' with the 20 cases\", iefimerida, 31-3-2020]</ref>\n\n=== April ===\n\n*On 1 April, 101 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1415. One more death from coronavirus was reported, bringing the country death toll to 50.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/213658/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 50 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 - 1.415 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-04-01|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n*On 2 April, 129 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1544. 27 new cases were reported in the general population, 23 in the Ritsona refugee and immigrant camp, and 79 new cases on the ship El. Venizelos which is being kept off the port of [[Piraeus]], bringing the total cases on the ship to 119. Three more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 53.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ethnos.gr/ygeia/97808_koronoios-53-thanatoi-sti-hora-mas-91-sti-meth-1544-synolika-ta-kroysmata|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 53 \u03b8\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03b9 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2, 91 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u039c\u0395\u0398, 1.544 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-04-02|website=ethnos.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n*On 3 April, it was announced that the total confirmed number of cases in the country was 1613. Six more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 59.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.in.gr/2020/04/03/greece/koronaios-deite-tin-enimerosi-apo-s-tsiodra-kai-n-xardalia-2/|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 : 99 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u2013 \u03a3\u03c4\u03b1 1.613 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u2013 59 \u03b8\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03b9 |last=Newsroom|date=2020-04-03|website=in.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n\n===COVID-19 Cases in Greece===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Date\n!Confirmed\nNew \n!Deaths\nNew\n!Confirmed\n\nTotal \n!Deaths\nTotal\n!Recoveries\n!Hospitalised\n!In Intensive Care \n(total on that date)\n!Cumulative total<br>tests performed\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 26 February\n|1\n| 0\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 27 February<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eody.gov.gr/enimerosi-diapisteymenon-syntakton-ygeias-gia-tis-exelixeis-anaforika-me-to-neo-koronoio/|title=\u0395\u03bd\u03b7\u03bc\u03ad\u03c1\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03b4\u03b9\u03b1\u03c0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c5\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03c9\u03bd \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03c4\u03ce\u03bd \u03a5\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b9\u03c2 \u03b5\u03be\u03b5\u03bb\u03af\u03be\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 \u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c6\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03bc\u03b5 \u03c4\u03bf \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc|date=2020-02-27|website=\u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2 \u039f\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2 \u0394\u03b7\u03bc\u03cc\u03c3\u03b9\u03b1\u03c2 \u03a5\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2|language=el|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n|2\n|0\n|3\n|0\