]&nbsp;\u2013 harmony and backing vocals, electric and acoustic guitars; [[fuzz bass]] {{small|(\"Under My Thumb\", \"Flight 505\", \"It's Not Easy\")}}\n*[[Brian Jones]]&nbsp;\u2013 electric and acoustic guitars; [[sitar]] {{small|(\"[[Paint It, Black]]\")}}, [[Appalachian dulcimer|dulcimer]] {{small|(\"Lady Jane\", \"I Am Waiting\")}}, harmonica {{small|(\"Goin' Home\", \"High and Dry\")}}, [[marimba]] {{small|(\"Under My Thumb\", \"Out of Time\")}}, [[Koto (instrument)|koto]] {{small|(\"Take It or Leave It\")}}{{sfn|Janovitz|2013|p=88}}\n*[[Bill Wyman]]&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar, fuzz bass; organ {{small|(\"Paint It, Black\")}}, bells\n*[[Charlie Watts]]&nbsp;\u2013 drums, percussion, bells\n\n'''Additional musicians'''\n*[[Jack Nitzsche]]&nbsp;\u2013 piano, organ, [[harpsichord]], percussion\n*[[Ian Stewart (musician)|Ian Stewart]]&nbsp;\u2013 piano, organ\n\n'''Additional personnel'''\n* [[David Bailey]]&nbsp;\u2013 photography {{small|(US edition)}}{{sfn|Anon. (b)|2002}}\n* [[Dave Hassinger]]&nbsp;\u2013 engineering\n* [[Andrew Loog Oldham]]&nbsp;\u2013 production, cover design {{small|(UK edition)}}{{sfn|Norman|2001|p=196}}\n* [[Jerry Schatzberg]]&nbsp;\u2013 photography\n* [[Guy Webster (photographer)|Guy Webster]]&nbsp;\u2013 photography {{small|(UK edition)}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1966)\n!Peak <br/>position\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |UK [[UK Albums Chart|''Record Retailer'' LPs Chart]]{{sfn|Anon. (d)|n.d.}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' Top LPs]]{{sfn|Havers|2018}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |US ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]]'' Top 100 Albums{{sfn|Anon. (d)|1966|p=41}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|West German [[Musikmarkt|''Musikmarkt'' LP Hit-Parade]]{{sfn|Anon. (b)|n.d.}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|}\n\n== Certifications ==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|artist=The Rolling Stones|title=Aftermath|award=Silver|type=album|certref={{sfn|Anon. (a)|n.d.}}}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|artist=The Rolling Stones|title=Aftermath|award=Platinum|type=album|certref={{sfn|Anon. (e)|n.d.}}}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|1960s|Rock music}}\n* [[British Invasion]]\n* [[Classic rock]]\n* [[List of rock albums]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Bibliography ==\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* {{cite magazine|ref=harv|first=Keith|last=Altham|title=The Rolling Stones' most favoured reporter reviews their fourth long-player track by track|date=8 April 1966|magazine=[[New Musical Express]]}}\n* {{cite magazine|ref={{SfnRef|Anon. (a)|1966}}|author=Anon.|title=The Rolling Stones: Aftermath (Decca)|date=16 April 1966|magazine=[[Melody Maker]]|url=https://rocksbackpages.com/Library/Article/the-rolling-stones-iaftermathi-decca-3|via=[[Rock's Backpages]]|accessdate=16 December 2019|url-access=subscription}}\n* {{cite magazine|ref={{SfnRef|Anon. (b)|1966}}|author=Anon.|title=Albums Reviews|magazine=[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]]|date=2 July 1966}}\n* {{cite magazine|ref={{SfnRef|Anon. (c)|1966}}|author=Anon.|title=Album Reviews|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=9 July 1966|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=9BAEAAAAMBAJ&q=Aftermath#v=snippet&q=Aftermath&f=false|accessdate=7 January 2020|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite magazine|ref={{SfnRef|Anon. (d)|1966}}|author=Anon.|date=13 August 1966|title=Top 100 Albums|magazine=Cash Box}}\n* {{cite magazine|ref=harv|author=Anon.|date=8 July 1995|title=Aftermath|magazine=NME}}\n* {{cite news|ref=harv|author=Anon.|date=1 January 2001|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/1400288/The-Sixties.html|title=The Sixties|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=27 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181127151909/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/1400288/The-Sixties.html|archive-date=27