h (magazine)|Clash]]|accessdate=27 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181128132652/https://www.clashmusic.com/features/classic-album-the-rolling-stones-aftermath|archive-date=28 November 2018|url-status=live}}\n* {{cite magazine|ref=harv|last=Hegeman|first=Bas|date=14 May 1966|title=From the Music Capitals of the World \u2013 Amsterdam|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=0ygEAAAAMBAJ&q=Aftermath#v=snippet&q=Aftermath&f=false|magazine=Billboard|accessdate=30 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181130202408/https://books.google.com.au/books?id=0ygEAAAAMBAJ&q=Aftermath#v=snippet&q=Aftermath&f=false|archive-date=30 November 2018|url-status=live|via=Google Books}}\n* {{cite web|ref=harv|last=Hull|first=Tom|authorlink=Tom Hull (critic)|date=n.d.|url=http://tomhull.com/ocston/nm/get_gl.php?n=The+Rolling+Stones|title=Grade List: The Rolling Stones|website=tomhull.com|accessdate=11 February 2020}}\n* {{cite web|last=Hyden|first=Steven|ref=harv|authorlink=Steven Hyden|date=3 April 2008|url=https://music.avclub.com/primer-the-rolling-stones-1798213682|title=Primer: The Rolling Stones|website=[[The A.V. Club]]|accessdate=1 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181202070608/https://music.avclub.com/primer-the-rolling-stones-1798213682|archive-date=2 December 2018|url-status=live}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Jagger|first1=Mick|last2=Richards|first2=Keith|last3=Watts|first3=Charlie|last4=Wood|first4=Ronnie|title=According to the Rolling Stones|publisher=Weidenfeld & Nicolson|location=London|year=2003|isbn=0-297-84332-X|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Janovitz|url=https://books.google.com/?id=tqC8BQAAQBAJ&pg=PT85&lpg=PT85&dq=Brian+JOnes+%22Take+It+or+Leave+It%22+koto#v=onepage&q=Brian%20JOnes%20%22Take%20It%20or%20Leave%20It%22%20koto&f=false|first=Bill|title=Rocks Off: 50 Tracks That Tell the Story of the Rolling Stones|publisher=St. Martin's Press|location=New York, NY|year=2013|isbn=978-1-250-02631-6|ref=harv|via=Google Books}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=King|first=Colin|year=2004|title=Rock On!: The Rock 'n' Roll Greats|publisher=Caxton|isbn=1840674733}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Kot|first=Greg|authorlink=Greg Kot|chapter=The Rolling Stones|editor1-last=Graff|editor1-first=Gary|editor2-last=Durchholz|editor2-first=Daniel|title=MusicHound Rock: The Essential Album Guide|publisher=Visible Ink Press|location=Farmington Hills, MI|year=1999|isbn=1-57859-061-2|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781578590612|url-access=registration}}\n* {{cite web|ref=harv|last=Kubernik|first=Harvey|title=Rubber Soul 50 Years On|publisher=Rock's Backpages|date=December 2015|url=http://www.rocksbackpages.com/Library/Article/irubber-souli-50-years-on-|url-access=subscription|accessdate=7 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629230900/https://www.rocksbackpages.com/Library/Article/irubber-souli-50-years-on-|archive-date=29 June 2019|url-status=live}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Larkin|first=Colin|authorlink=Colin Larkin|title=All Time Top 1000 Albums|publisher=[[Virgin Books]]|date=2000|edition=3rd|isbn=0-7535-0493-6|title-link=All Time Top 1000 Albums}}\n* {{cite book|last=Larkin|first=Colin|title=Encyclopedia of Popular Music|publisher=Omnibus Press|location=London|year=2011|isbn=978-0-85712-595-8|ref=harv|title-link=Encyclopedia of Popular Music}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|first=Shawn|last=Levy|authorlink=Shawn Levy (writer)|title=Ready, Steady, Go!: Swinging London and the Invention of Cool |publisher=Fourth Estate|location=London|year=2002|isbn=978-1-84115-226-4}}\n* {{cite magazine|ref=harv|last=MacDonald|first=Ian|title=The Rolling Stones: Play With Fire|date=November 2002|magazine=[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]|url=https://www.rocksbackpages.com/Library/Article/the-rolling-stones-play-with-fire|via=[[Rock's Backpages]]|accessdate=21 July 2018|url-access=subscription}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Malvinni|first=David|year=2016|title=Experiencing the Rolling Stones: A Listener'