 Rock and Pop Artists from Vaudeville to Techno|publisher=[[Harvard University Press]]|isbn=0674443187}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Clayson|first=Alan|authorlink=Alan Clayson|year=2006|title=The Rolling Stones Album File & Complete Discography|publisher=Cassell Illustrated|isbn=1844034941}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Clayson|first=Alan|year=2007|title=Legendary Sessions: The Rolling Stones: Beggars Banquet|publisher=Billboard Books|isbn=978-0823083978|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/rollingstonesbeg00clay}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Coates|first=Norma|year=2019|chapter=How can a smart chick like me listen to the Stones and not throw up? A speculative exploration of Beggars Banquet and misogyny|editor-last=Reising|editor-first=Russell|title=Beggars Banquet and the Rolling Stones' Rock and Roll Revolution: 'They Call My Name Disturbance'|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1351396417}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Courrier|first=Kevin|year=2008|title=Artificial Paradise: The Dark Side of the Beatles' Utopian Dream: The Dark Side of the Beatles' Utopian Dream|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-0313345876}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Dalton|first=David|year=1982|title=The Rolling Stones|publisher=Delilah/Putnam Books|isbn=0399410058}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Davis|first=Stephen|authorlink=Stephen Davis (music journalist)|year=2001|title=Old Gods Almost Dead: The 40-Year Odyssey of the Rolling Stones|publisher=Crown/Archetype|isbn=0767909569}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last1=DeRogatis|first1=Jim|authorlink1=Jim DeRogatis|last2=Kot|first2=Greg|authorlink2=Greg Kot|year=2010|title=The Beatles vs. The Rolling Stones: Sound Opinions On the Great Rock 'N' Roll Rivalry|publisher=[[Voyageur Press]]|isbn=1610605136}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|editor-last=Dimery|editor-first=Robert|year=2010|title=1001 Albums You Must Hear Before You Die|edition=Revised and updated|publisher=Universe|isbn=978-0-7893-2074-2|title-link=1001 Albums You Must Hear Before You Die}}\